    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# 03 - Model Training\\n\\nTrains and compares four classifiers on the feature dataset (`data/processed/features.csv`): a **Gaussian classifier written from scratch** (as in the course lab), **kNN**, **SVM (RBF)** and **MLP**.\\n\\nPipeline in the order taught in the course (lab04): split -> scaling (estimated only on the training set) -> hyperparameter optimization with cross-validation -> training -> evaluation.\\n\\n> First cell: sets the working directory. Then Restart & Run All.\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"33e527e0bc55535a\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:03.902926200Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:02.968575700Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import os\\nwhile not os.path.isdir('data') and os.getcwd() != os.path.dirname(os.getcwd()):\\n    os.chdir('..')\\nprint('Working dir:', os.getcwd())\\n\\nimport numpy as np\\nimport pandas as pd\\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\nimport seaborn as sns\\nfrom scipy.stats import multivariate_normal\\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, GridSearchCV\\nfrom sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler, LabelEncoder\\nfrom sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\\nfrom sklearn.svm import SVC\\nfrom sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier\\nfrom sklearn.neural_network import MLPClassifier\\nfrom sklearn.metrics import (classification_report, confusion_matrix,\\n                             balanced_accuracy_score, f1_score)\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a6f00d13f353974e\",\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n",
    "     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n",
    "     \"text\": [\n",
    "      \"Working dir: C:\\\\Users\\\\Matteo\\\\Desktop\\\\Cybersecurity\\\\2_Sem\\\\Machine Learning\\\\Progetto\\\\Git.py_project\\n\"\n",
    "     ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 1\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Load the features and prepare X and y\\n`X` = the 25 numerical feature columns. `y` = the class. We turn the 4 text labels into numbers 0..3 with LabelEncoder (needed by the Gaussian classifier we write ourselves).\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"9c7d403b4d605560\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:04.140306700Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:03.902926200Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"data = pd.read_csv('data/processed/features.csv')\\nX = data.drop(columns=['type'])\\nle = LabelEncoder()\\ny = le.fit_transform(data['type'])\\nprint('Features:', X.shape[1], '| Samples:', X.shape[0])\\nprint('Classes:', list(le.classes_))\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"94aed57a80bf540b\",\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n",
    "     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n",
    "     \"text\": [\n",
    "      \"Features: 25 | Samples: 15000\\n\",\n",
    "      \"Classes: ['benign', 'defacement', 'malware', 'phishing']\\n\"\n",
    "     ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 2\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Train / test split\\nWe set aside 20% of the data as a test set: the model never sees it during training, so the final evaluation is honest (no hidden overfitting). `stratify=y` keeps the proportions of the 4 classes in both groups, which is essential because the classes are imbalanced.\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"3f899672063af083\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:04.241677800Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:04.155931Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\\n    X, y, test_size=0.2, stratify=y, random_state=42)\\nprint('Train:', X_train.shape, '| Test:', X_test.shape)\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c9254d3cb56954dc\",\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n",
    "     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n",
    "     \"text\": [\n",
    "      \"Train: (12000, 25) | Test: (3000, 25)\\n\"\n",
    "     ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 3\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Feature scaling\\nFeatures have different scales (e.g. `url_length` ~30-200 vs `has_https` 0/1). SVM, kNN and MLP are sensitive to scale: without normalization, features with large numbers would dominate. We use MinMaxScaler **estimated only on the training set** and applied to the test set too (never the other way around: that would be leakage). For kNN/SVM/MLP with GridSearchCV the scaler goes inside the Pipeline; here we prepare the scaled version for the 'manual' Gaussian.\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"96a4b0f81b58026b\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:04.383547900Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:04.241677800Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"scaler = MinMaxScaler().fit(X_train)\\nX_train_s = scaler.transform(X_train)\\nX_test_s = scaler.transform(X_test)\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"976755eac3e5f51d\",\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 4\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Gaussian classifier written from scratch (from the course lab)\\nFor each class it estimates, with maximum likelihood: the prior probability (how frequent the class is), the mean vector and the covariance matrix of the features. To classify a URL, it computes for each class the log-likelihood + log-prior and picks the class with the highest score. We add a small regularization (`+1e-6*I`) to the covariance to avoid singular matrices (which happen with binary features that have zero variance within a class).\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"ffd92378366f5c57\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:04.415790400Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:04.399168200Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"class CClassifierGaussian:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Gaussian classifier with maximum-likelihood estimates (full covariance).\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    def fit(self, x, y):\\n        x = np.asarray(x, dtype=float)\\n        self.classes_ = np.unique(y)\\n        d = x.shape[1]\\n        self._priors, self._means, self._covs = [], [], []\\n        for k in self.classes_:\\n            xk = x[y == k]\\n            self._priors.append(len(xk) / len(x))\\n            self._means.append(xk.mean(axis=0))\\n            self._covs.append(np.cov(xk.T) + 1e-6 * np.eye(d))  # regularization\\n        return self\\n\\n    def _scores(self, x):\\n        s = [multivariate_normal(m, c, allow_singular=True).logpdf(x) + np.log(p)\\n             for m, c, p in zip(self._means, self._covs, self._priors)]\\n        return np.array(s).T  # (n_samples, n_classes)\\n\\n    def predict(self, x):\\n        x = np.asarray(x, dtype=float)\\n        return self.classes_[np.argmax(self._scores(x), axis=1)]\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"715518a1a789ce13\",\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 5\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Results collector + evaluation function\\nFor each model we compute **balanced accuracy** and **macro-F1** (the right metrics with imbalanced classes, where plain accuracy is misleading) and the per-class report.\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"5e135e8020050124\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:04.440989200Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:04.415790400Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"results = {}\\n\\ndef evaluate(name, y_pred):\\n    ba = balanced_accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)\\n    mf1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred, average='macro')\\n    results[name] = {'balanced_acc': round(ba, 3), 'macro_f1': round(mf1, 3)}\\n    print(f'\\\\n=== {name} ===')\\n    print('Balanced accuracy:', round(ba, 3), '| Macro-F1:', round(mf1, 3))\\n    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=le.classes_, zero_division=0))\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"3b140c9ee960f41\",\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 6\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:04.554350100Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:04.440989200Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Gaussian (from scratch)\\ngauss = CClassifierGaussian().fit(X_train_s, y_train)\\nevaluate('Gaussian', gauss.predict(X_test_s))\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"99925a3290c0fce\",\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n",
    "     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n",
    "     \"text\": [\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"=== Gaussian ===\\n\",\n",
    "      \"Balanced accuracy: 0.583 | Macro-F1: 0.503\\n\",\n",
    "      \"              precision    recall  f1-score   support\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"      benign       0.82      0.40      0.53      2003\\n\",\n",
    "      \"  defacement       0.24      0.98      0.38       446\\n\",\n",
    "      \"     malware       0.94      0.82      0.88       111\\n\",\n",
    "      \"    phishing       0.71      0.13      0.22       440\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"    accuracy                           0.46      3000\\n\",\n",
    "      \"   macro avg       0.68      0.58      0.50      3000\\n\",\n",
    "      \"weighted avg       0.72      0.46      0.48      3000\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\"\n",
    "     ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 7\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## kNN, SVM, MLP with hyperparameter optimization (GridSearchCV, 5-fold)\\nFor kNN and SVM we search the best hyperparameters with grid search + 5-fold cross-validation (as in lab04). The scaler is inside the Pipeline: this way it is re-estimated at each fold, with no leakage. We optimize for `balanced_accuracy` given the class imbalance.\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"5dde640d853d72d8\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:24.092705300Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:04.564304700Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"knn = GridSearchCV(\\n    Pipeline([('scaler', MinMaxScaler()), ('clf', KNeighborsClassifier())]),\\n    {'clf__n_neighbors': [3, 5, 7, 11]},\\n    cv=5, scoring='balanced_accuracy', n_jobs=-1).fit(X_train, y_train)\\nprint('Best k:', knn.best_params_)\\nevaluate('kNN', knn.predict(X_test))\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"3d3ce65072dc16db\",\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n",
    "     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n",
    "     \"text\": [\n",
    "      \"Best k: {'clf__n_neighbors': 3}\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"=== kNN ===\\n\",\n",
    "      \"Balanced accuracy: 0.8 | Macro-F1: 0.817\\n\",\n",
    "      \"              precision    recall  f1-score   support\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"      benign       0.89      0.93      0.91      2003\\n\",\n",
    "      \"  defacement       0.83      0.80      0.81       446\\n\",\n",
    "      \"     malware       0.90      0.86      0.88       111\\n\",\n",
    "      \"    phishing       0.73      0.62      0.67       440\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"    accuracy                           0.86      3000\\n\",\n",
    "      \"   macro avg       0.84      0.80      0.82      3000\\n\",\n",
    "      \"weighted avg       0.86      0.86      0.86      3000\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\"\n",
    "     ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 8\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:04:48.168001900Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:03:24.137196800Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# NB: the RBF-kernel SVM can take a few minutes on 12,000 samples. This is normal.\\nsvm = GridSearchCV(\\n    Pipeline([('scaler', MinMaxScaler()), ('clf', SVC(kernel='rbf'))]),\\n    {'clf__C': [1, 10], 'clf__gamma': ['scale', 0.1]},\\n    cv=5, scoring='balanced_accuracy', n_jobs=-1).fit(X_train, y_train)\\nprint('Best SVM parameters:', svm.best_params_)\\nevaluate('SVM (RBF)', svm.predict(X_test))\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"6e6ba4def8d5321a\",\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n",
    "     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n",
    "     \"text\": [\n",
    "      \"Best SVM parameters: {'clf__C': 10, 'clf__gamma': 'scale'}\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"=== SVM (RBF) ===\\n\",\n",
    "      \"Balanced accuracy: 0.78 | Macro-F1: 0.809\\n\",\n",
    "      \"              precision    recall  f1-score   support\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"      benign       0.88      0.96      0.92      2003\\n\",\n",
    "      \"  defacement       0.84      0.88      0.86       446\\n\",\n",
    "      \"     malware       0.96      0.84      0.89       111\\n\",\n",
    "      \"    phishing       0.78      0.44      0.57       440\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"    accuracy                           0.87      3000\\n\",\n",
    "      \"   macro avg       0.86      0.78      0.81      3000\\n\",\n",
    "      \"weighted avg       0.86      0.87      0.86      3000\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\"\n",
    "     ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 9\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:05:19.431448800Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-07-15T17:04:48.168001900Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"mlp = Pipeline([\\n    ('scaler', MinMaxScaler()),\\n    ('clf', MLPClassifier(hidden_layer_sizes=(32, 16), max_iter=500, random_state=42))\\n]).fit(X_train, y_train)\\nevaluate('MLP', mlp.predict(X_test))\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"7744e6b3bc19f30e\",\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n",
    "     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n",
    "     \"text\": [\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"=== MLP ===\\n\",\n",
    "      \"Balanced accuracy: 0.852 | Macro-F1: 0.873\\n\",\n",
    "      \"              precision    recall  f1-score   support\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"      benign       0.93      0.96      0.95      2003\\n\",\n",
    "      \"  defacement       0.94      0.91      0.92       446\\n\",\n",
    "      \"     malware       0.95      0.83      0.88       111\\n\",\n",
    "      \"    phishing       0.76      0.71      0.74       440\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"    accuracy                           0.91      3000\\n\",\n",
